{
  "texts": [
    "However, as indicated by the green cell colors, the range query processing time for Flood, LISA and IFI are all less than that of ZMI.",
    "The reason is that the above three learned indexes have a better capability of pruning unnecessary candidates given a specific query range, leading to less memory footprint (i.e., small total cache references count).",
    "As an example, the count of total cache references (e.g., 50M, 46M, and 47M for IFI, LISA and Flood, respectively) are all smaller than the 73M references produced by ZMI.",
    "As a consequence, the overall effect of smaller total cache references results in fewer query processing costs.",
    "There is a general positive correlation between the query processing time and the CPU performance counters (CR, CMR, BR, BMR)."
  ]
}